EXTRACTED VALUE: Tougher rivals that only improve an excellent game to the point of making it essential. [Issue #6]
All things told Condemned 2 is a good sequel that does manage to do the first game justice on most counts.
The Burnout franchise risks a new direction, and comes one sequel away from perfection.
EA have delivered a superb-looking game but unfortunately the gooey, cumbersome controls have let the game down badly.
